 a differentiated iPhone app from a researched app opportunity using SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\"\nworkflows/iphone-app-factory/build-iphone-app.daytona.toml:16:boilerplate_repo = \"SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Distribution\"\nscripts/iphone-app-factory/bootstrap.mjs:13:const boilerplateRepo = arg(\"--boilerplate-repo\", \"SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Distribution\");\nscripts/iphone-app-factory/bootstrap.mjs:83:  boilerplateRepo,\nscripts/iphone-app-factory/bootstrap.mjs:89:    \"SwiftAIBoilerplatePro is extended instead of rebuilding platform infrastructure\",\nscripts/iphone-app-factory/bootstrap.mjs:116:  `# iPhone App Factory Context\\n\\nApp: ${appName}\\nBundle ID: ${bundleId}\\nOutput: ${appDir}\\nBoilerplate: ${boilerplateRepo}\\n\\nUse the quality bar in quality-bar.json as blocking requirements.\\n`\nscripts/iphone-app-factory/bootstrap.mjs:119:console.log(JSON.stringify({ ok: true, appDir, appName, bundleId, boilerplateRepo, secretShellGuards }));\nscripts/iphone-app-factory/boilerplate-contract-gate.mjs:16:if (!has(\"SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj\")) {\nscripts/iphone-app-factory/boilerplate-contract-gate.mjs:22:  if (!has(`Packages/${pkg}`)) failures.push(`missing required boilerplate package Packages/${pkg}`);\nscripts/iphone-app-factory/boilerplate-contract-gate.mjs:26:for (const marker of [\"CompositionRoot\", \"DesignSystem\", \"SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\"]) {\nscripts/iphone-app-factory/boilerplate-contract-gate.mjs:27:  if (!architecture.includes(marker)) failures.push(`architecture missing boilerplate marker ${marker}`);\nscripts/iphone-app-factory/boilerplate-contract-gate.mjs:31:writeFileSync(`${root}/boilerplate-contract.json`, `${JSON.stringify(report, null, 2)}\\n`);\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:5:**Boilerplate**: SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Distribution  \n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:10:## ADR-001: Extend SwiftAIBoilerplatePro — Do Not Rebuild Platform Infrastructure\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:12:**Decision**: WakeTask extends `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` exclusively. No core platform components (Authentication, Networking, Storage, Payments, AI, Localization, FeatureSettings, DesignSystem) are rebuilt within the application boundary.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:16:- The product spec states: \"The application MUST forcefully leverage the `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` repository. Rebuilding core infrastructure is strictly forbidden.\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:17:- Boilerplate modules are production-tested; modifying them risks cascading bugs and breaks the update path for future boilerplate releases.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:18:- Compliance is validated via a CI-blocking `boilerplate-integrity-check.mjs` script that scans for redundant implementations.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:21:- Partial rebuild of Networking and Auth: Rejected — WakeTask has no custom auth or networking requirements; the boilerplate already provides these.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:22:- Fork the boilerplate: Rejected — forking breaks the extension model and makes boilerplate updates impossible.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:28:**Decision**: All boilerplate packages remain in the project:\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:34:| `Packages/Storage` | Kept (extended) | WakeTask entities share the boilerplate persistence stack |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:42:| `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj` | Kept (renamed) | Renamed to `WakeTask.xcodeproj` after bootstrap |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:45:**App Store 4.3 Consequence**: Removing boilerplate modules would reduce the app's codebase to a minimal alarm utility — structurally similar to alarm apps already on the App Store. By retaining the full boilerplate surface area (payments, AI, auth, networking, design system, localization), WakeTask presents itself as a **full-featured platform app**, not a single-purpose widget. This, combined with the behavioral psychology differentiators in metadata, materially reduces 4.3 spam-rejection risk.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:60:**Decision**: All WakeTask-specific services are registered as extensions to the boilerplate's `CompositionRoot` DI container. The pattern is:\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:62:1. Create `WakeTaskComposition.swift` (new file, no boilerplate edits).\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:67:- Preserves the boilerplate's established DI pattern.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:68:- Zero edits to boilerplate source files.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:76:**Decision**: The boilerplate **must** be acquired into `apps/waketask-iphone` before any WakeTask-specific code is written. This is done via:\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:83:  --boilerplate-repo 'SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Distribution'\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:86:The scratch `apps/waketask-iphone` directory is empty at project start. The bootstrap script clones/copies the boilerplate distribution, renames the Xcode project, updates the bundle ID, and validates that all packages are intact.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:176:| ADR-001 | Extend SwiftAIBoilerplatePro — no rebuilds | All packages kept | Accepted |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:177:| ADR-002 | Keep all boilerplate modules — no removals | Core, Networking, Storage, Auth, Payments, AI, FeatureSettings, Localization, DesignSystem, CompositionRoot, SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj, Config/App.xcconfig all intact | Accepted |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:182:| ADR-007 | Challenge modalities with accessibility fallbacks | No boilerplate changes | Accepted |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md:183:| ADR-008 | Social Witness scaffolded, delivery v1.1 | No boilerplate changes | Accepted |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:5:**Boilerplate**: SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Distribution  \n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:13:`apps/waketask-iphone` starts empty. Before any WakeTask-specific code is written, the boilerplate is acquired:\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:20:  --boilerplate-repo 'SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Distribution'\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:23:This clones/copies `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Distribution` into `apps/waketask-iphone` with:\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:25:- **SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj** — pre-configured Xcode project\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:27:- All boilerplate **Packages/** intact (Core, Networking, Storage, Auth, Payments, AI, FeatureSettings, Localization, DesignSystem)\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:31:The project is then renamed to `WakeTask.xcodeproj` and the bundle ID is set to `com.keen.waketask`. All subsequent architecture decisions **extend — never replace** this base.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:41:| **SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj** | `./WakeTask.xcodeproj` | Project structure, build settings, target definitions — renamed to `WakeTask.xcodeproj` after bootstrap |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:46:| **Packages/Auth** | `Packages/Auth/` | Authentication workflows, credential management — used as-is if boilerplate provides onboarding; no custom auth added |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:70:All WakeTask-specific packages (`AlarmScheduler`, `TaskEngine`, `AdaptiveDifficultyEngine`, `ChallengeOrchestrator`, `WakeConfirmationScheduler`) register into the CompositionRoot container and depend on the boilerplate packages above.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:79:// WakeTaskComposition.swift — new file, no boilerplate edits\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:102:| Alarm Schedule Editor | `FeatureSettings` rows, `DatePicker`, `Toggle` | Uses boilerplate settings scaffold |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:114:New SwiftData entities added **alongside** existing boilerplate models:\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:195:├── WakeTask.xcodeproj/            # Renamed from SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:198:├── Packages/                      # All boilerplate packages — UNCHANGED\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:226:│   └── boilerplate-integrity-check.mjs\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:252:| Boilerplate integrity | `boilerplate-integrity-check.mjs` | ✅ Yes |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:284:            -project WakeTask.xcodeproj -scheme WakeTask \\\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:292:            -project WakeTask.xcodeproj -scheme WakeTask \\\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:308:        run: node scripts/iphone-app-factory/boilerplate-integrity-check.mjs --project apps/waketask-iphone\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md:343:1. **Phase 0** — Acquire boilerplate, validate Xcode project builds on macOS CI\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:5:**Strategy**: Extend SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Distribution instead of rebuilding  \n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:22:**Do not rebuild**. SwiftAIBoilerplatePro provides battle-tested infrastructure for Auth, Networking, Storage, Payments, AI, Design System, Localization, Settings, and CompositionRoot patterns. WakeTask is a **vertical slice** on top of this foundation.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:29:- **SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj** — Project structure, build settings\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1275:- ✅ No custom Auth layer (uses boilerplate Auth package)\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1276:- ✅ No custom Networking layer (uses boilerplate Networking abstractions)\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1278:- ✅ No custom Payments (uses boilerplate StoreKit 2 integration)\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1279:- ✅ No custom Localization engine (uses boilerplate i18n)\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1280:- ✅ No custom DesignSystem (extends boilerplate tokens and components)\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1284:**Validation Script**: `scripts/iphone-app-factory/boilerplate-integrity-check.mjs`\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1332:**Before any WakeTask-specific code is added, the boilerplate must be acquired:**\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1336:# scripts/iphone-app-factory/setup-boilerplate.sh\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1341:BOILERPLATE_REPO=\"${2:-SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Distribution}\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1348:# Clone boilerplate into app directory\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1354:echo \"Copying boilerplate to $APP_DIR\"\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1359:mv SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj WakeTask.xcodeproj\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1374:  --boilerplate-repo 'SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Distribution'\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1378:- ✅ `apps/waketask-iphone/` contains cloned boilerplate\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1379:- ✅ Project renamed to `WakeTask.xcodeproj`\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1381:- ✅ All boilerplate packages intact and unmodified\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1387:1. **Phase 0: Setup** → Clone boilerplate, validate Xcode project builds\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1431:| **Boilerplate (Preserved)** | SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj, Core, Networking, Storage, Auth, Payments, AI, Localization, DesignSystem | ✅ Unchanged | Zero modifications; foundational framework |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1439:| **Validation** | App Store 4.3 audit, boilerplate integrity check | 🆕 New Scripts | Differentiation and platform compliance |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1447:This architecture extends SwiftAIBoilerplatePro decisively. WakeTask is a **vertical slice** that:\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1448:- **Preserves** all boilerplate infrastructure (zero redundancy)\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-claude.md:1454:**Ready for implementation**. All architectural decisions are traceable to boilerplate constraints, specification requirements, and research evidence.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:6:**Boilerplate**: SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Distribution  \n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:20:  --boilerplate-repo 'SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Distribution'\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:23:This clones the boilerplate distribution into `apps/waketask-iphone` with a pre-configured Xcode project, Swift Package dependencies, CI scaffolding, SwiftLint/SwiftFormat/Qlty hooks, and the DesignSystem + CompositionRoot pattern. All subsequent architecture decisions extend — never replace — this base.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:29:These modules are used as-is from SwiftAIBoilerplatePro. No modifications, no forks, no re-implementations.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:37:| **Auth** | User authentication flow, session management, secure keychain storage | Used as-is if the boilerplate provides onboarding/login. WakeTask does not add custom auth. |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:44:The quality-bar (`quality-bar.json`) explicitly forbids rebuilding auth, payments, AI, storage, networking, localization, settings, or design system without ADR approval. Keeping these unchanged preserves SwiftAIBoilerplatePro update compatibility and satisfies the spec's \"Boilerplate Compliance\" acceptance criterion.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:50:These modules are extended via composition — new Swift files, new types registered in the DI container, new views using existing DesignSystem primitives. No existing boilerplate source files are edited.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:54:WakeTask adds the following services, registered alongside existing boilerplate services in the CompositionRoot assembly:\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:77:New SwiftData/CoreData entities are added *alongside* existing boilerplate models. These track:\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:86:These share the same persistence stack and container configuration already present in the boilerplate.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:98:These are new `View` structs composed with the boilerplate's `SettingsRow`, `ToggleRow`, `SliderRow` components.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:104:**None.** All boilerplate packages remain in the project. The only justification for removal would be if a package added measurable binary size or compile-time overhead, which is not the case for a Swift Package that simply contributes symbols. Unused packages (e.g., AI) are left in place for future feature parity and to avoid destabilizing the boilerplate's package dependency graph.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:110:The boilerplate's `CompositionRoot` is the single assembly point. WakeTask's additions follow the existing pattern:\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:113:2. **ViewModel Wiring**: Each WakeTask ViewModel receives its dependencies via the container — consistent with the boilerplate's MVVM pattern.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:114:3. **Router/Navigation**: WakeTask adds a new root destination (`AlarmView` or `HomeView`) to the boilerplate's app router, replacing the boilerplate's demo landing screen. The router structure itself is unchanged.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:118:// WakeTaskServices.swift — new file, no boilerplate edits\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:136:| **Alarm Schedule Editor** | `Settings` package rows, `DatePicker` wrapper, `Toggle` | Uses boilerplate settings scaffold |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:157:- **Repositories** follow the boilerplate's existing `RepositoryProtocol` pattern.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:158:- **Concrete repositories** use the boilerplate's persistence abstraction (SwiftData/CoreData).\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:195:Each screen is owned by a single `@Observable` ViewModel (iOS 17+ observation, or `ObservableObject` if the boilerplate targets iOS 15/16). ViewModel responsibilities are strictly scoped:\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:202:| `SettingsViewModel` | SettingsView (extends boilerplate) | `TaskHistoryRepository`, `DifficultyRepository` | Task toggles, difficulty range, timer prefs |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:219:| **`Sendable` conformance** | `AlarmSchedule`, `SnoozeRecord`, `DifficultyState`, `TaskHistory` are value types (structs) sent across actors (UI ↔ repository ↔ scheduler). | All model structs conform to `Sendable`. `CoreMotionManager` wrapper uses `@unchecked Sendable` with an internal `OSAllocatedUnfairLock` or `actor` isolation — whichever the boilerplate standard dictates. |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:357:      - name: Install boilerplate dependencies\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:359:          # If boilerplate uses SPM packages, resolve them\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:382:            -project WakeTask.xcodeproj \\\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:394:            -project WakeTask.xcodeproj \\\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:494:| Keep all boilerplate packages unchanged | quality-bar forbids rebuild; preserves update path | No |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:495:| Add WakeTask-specific entities via new Swift files | Extends boilerplate without modifying it | No |\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:510:├── WakeTask.xcodeproj/            # From boilerplate bootstrap\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:584:├── .swiftlint.yml                 # From boilerplate\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:585:├── .swiftformat                   # From boilerplate\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture-codex.md:592:*This architecture candidate is identified as `architecture-codex` for the WakeTask iPhone app. It extends SwiftAIBoilerplatePro without rebuilding any platform infrastructure, enforces Swift 6 strict concurrency, defines a comprehensive test and CI strategy, and includes Appium exploratory validation as a blocking gate.*\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-red-team.md:4:The generated spec, definition of done, and consensus files adequately cover the requirement for the WakeTask iOS application. The specifications explicitly mandate `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` reuse without rebuilding platform infrastructure, integrate Appium/XCUITest exploratory QA gates, enforce Guideline 4.3 differentiation to defeat App Store spam filters, and include all the core anti-habituation logic correctly extracted from research synthesis and the viable candidates. The off-topic Claude routines app drift has been rejected and the core mechanic (task rotation, escalating difficulty, calm down post-dismiss check) is sound.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-red-team.md:9:4.  **Boilerplate Reuse**: The spec explicitly mandates using `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` for core infrastructure and forbids rebuilding it.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md:31:    - [ ] Validation scripts confirm that the app extends `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` mechanics.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:26:The application MUST forcefully leverage the `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` repository. Rebuilding core infrastructure is strictly forbidden.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:27:*   **Auth/Data:** Do NOT rebuild authentication or persistence. Use the boilerplate's provided data layer and models.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:28:*   **Networking/AI:** Use the boilerplate's networking abstractions and AI integration points if needed (though the core alarm mechanic should function offline).\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md:29:*   **UI/Design System:** Utilize the boilerplate's foundational UI components (buttons, typography, layout containers), localization handlers, and settings screens.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md:10:4.  **Boilerplate Reuse (`SwiftAIBoilerplatePro`):** The app must extensively utilize the `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` foundation. We do not rebuild authentication, data persistence, network scaffolding, AI SDK wiring, or core design system components. We build *on top* of them.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:5:We have independent spec candidates generated across parallel branches. This critique evaluates their alignment with the core opportunity, technical feasibility, and alignment with factory boilerplate rules.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:10:- **Strengths:** Explicitly tackles task-based dismissal, anti-snooze friction, and adaptive difficulty. Strongly focuses on Appium/XCUITest QA, App Store 4.3 differentiation (avoiding simple generic clones), and accurately calls out `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` reuse constraints.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:15:- **Strengths:** Excellent definition of concrete challenge modules. Solid CI, macOS GitHub validation, and adherence to boilerplate reuse constraints without unnecessary infrastructural rebuilds.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:32:- `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` must be leveraged. There is no excuse to rebuild underlying infrastructure (auth, networking, AI, etc.).\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:37:- **Boilerplate Rebuild Risk:** Without strict boundaries, candidates might detail building entirely new persistence models or AI integrations from scratch. The final spec must explicitly restrict the agent from rebuilding what the boilerplate provides.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md:64:12. **Explicit SwiftAIBoilerplatePro reuse:** Zero rebuilding of auth, payments, AI, storage, networking, localization, settings, or the core design system.\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:9:        \"raw\": \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{{prompt_registry}}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{{golden_cases}}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n{{spec_consensus}}\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n{{architecture_consensus}}\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n{{implement_integration}}\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n{{ai_ui_explorer}}\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n{{final_consensus}}\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:10:        \"label\": \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{{prompt_registry}}\\n\\nGolden cases:\\n{{golden_cases}}\\n\\nRepresentative prompts:\\nSPEC_CONSENSUS:\\n{{spec_consensus}}\\n\\nARCHITECTURE:\\n{{architecture_consensus}}\\n\\nIMPLEMENT_INTEGRATION:\\n{{implement_integration}}\\n\\nAI_UI_EXPLORER:\\n{{ai_ui_explorer}}\\n\\nFINAL_CONSENSUS:\\n{{final_consensus}}\\n\\nReturn valid JSON only, no markdown fences:\\n{\\\"verdict\\\":\\\"APPROVE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.0,\\\"covered\\\":[\\\"spec_lab\\\",\\\"boilerplate_reuse\\\",\\\"ios_quality\\\",\\\"appium_qa\\\",\\\"mobbin_safety\\\",\\\"release_hardening\\\"],\\\"gaps\\\":[]}\\n\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:75:              \"reason\": \"Expected output to contain all of [spec_lab, boilerplate_reuse, ios_quality, appium_qa, mobbin_safety, release_hardening]. Missing: [spec_lab, boilerplate_reuse, ios_quality, appium_qa, mobbin_safety, release_hardening]\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:80:                  \"boilerplate_reuse\",\n.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evals/promptfoo-output.json:117:          \"raw\": \"Evaluate whether this iPhone App Factory prompt suite is strong enough for overnight agentic app generation.\\n\\nPrompt registry:\\n{\\n  \\\"workflow\\\": \\\"iphone-app-factory\\\",\\n  \\\"dataset_version\\\": \\\"iphone-app-factory-prompts-v1\\\",\\n  \\\"rubric_version\\\": \\\"iphone-app-factory-prompt-rubric-v1\\\",\\n  \\\"prompts\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/research-app-store.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"research\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"App Store\\\", \\\"reviews\\\", \\\"evidence quality\\\", \\\"do not invent\\\", \\\"never print environment variables\\\", \\\"environment dump commands\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/research-reddit.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"research\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"Reddit\\\", \\\"source links\\\", \\\"do not fabricate\\\", \\\"never print environment variables\\\", \\\"environment dump commands\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-factory/research-competitors.md\\\",\\n      \\\"stage\\\": \\\"research\\\",\\n      \\\"must_include\\\": [\\\"competitor\\\", \\\"positioning\\\", \\\"evidence quality\\\", \\\"never print environment variables\\\", \\\"environment dump commands\\\"]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"prompts/iphone-app-f